# Postcondition Validation

Apply validation rules from [docs/validation-rules.md](../../docs/validation-rules.md) to every code change.

## Quick Reference

| Change Type | Command |
|-------------|---------|
| Single file | `make check-sanity FILES="${FILE_PATH}"` |
| Multi-file | `make check-sanity` |
| Refactor | `make refactor && make test` |
| Behavior change | `make behavior` |
| Pre-commit | `make prepr` |

## Must Pass
- golangci linters: dupl, gocyclo, goconst, unparam, ineffassign, nestif
- no new lint errors introduced
- tests pass if behavior changed

## Test Files
Do not target test files directly. Target the package or include source files:
```bash
# Correct
make check-sanity FILES="./path/to/package"
```
